  <entry>
    <title type="html"><![CDATA[Create QR Codes in Ruby on Rails Application]]></title>
    <link href="http://geekhmer.github.io/blog/2015/04/15/create-qr-codes-in-ruby-on-rails-application/"/>
    <updated>2015-04-15T11:34:00+07:00</updated>
    <id>http://geekhmer.github.io/blog/2015/04/15/create-qr-codes-in-ruby-on-rails-application</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>
  <img src="http://geekhmer.github.io/images/ruby_on_rails.png" width="400" alt="Create QR Codes in Ruby on Rails Application" />
</p>




<p>
  <a href="https://rubygems.org/gems/barby" target="_blank">Barby</a> is a great gem for generating a barcode or QR code. You can choose to output it as any number of barcode types or as a QR code. This example will use a QR code but I have successfully used the Code128 barcode which is fairly common in the retail space.
</p>




<p>
  Add Barby to your gem file:
</p>


<p><div class='bogus-wrapper'><notextile><figure class='code'><figcaption><span>Gemfile </span></figcaption>
 <div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='ruby'><span class='line'><span class="n">gem</span> <span class="o">&amp;</span><span class="n">lsquo</span><span class="p">;</span><span class="n">barby</span><span class="o">&amp;</span><span class="n">rsquo</span><span class="p">;,</span>  <span class="o">&amp;</span><span class="n">lsquo</span><span class="p">;</span><span class="o">~&gt;</span> <span class="mi">0</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="mi">6</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="mi">2</span><span class="o">&amp;</span><span class="n">rsquo</span><span class="p">;</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="n">gem</span> <span class="o">&amp;</span><span class="n">lsquo</span><span class="p">;</span><span class="n">rqrcode</span><span class="o">&amp;</span><span class="n">rsquo</span><span class="p">;,</span><span class="o">&amp;</span><span class="n">lsquo</span><span class="p">;</span><span class="o">~&gt;</span> <span class="mi">0</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="mi">4</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="mi">2</span><span class="o">&amp;</span><span class="n">rsquo</span><span class="p">;</span>
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure></notextile></div></p>

<p>
  Here is an example helper for generating the QR code as base64 encoded png data:
</p>


<p><div class='bogus-wrapper'><notextile><figure class='code'> <div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
<span class='line-number'>5</span>
<span class='line-number'>6</span>
<span class='line-number'>7</span>
<span class='line-number'>8</span>
<span class='line-number'>9</span>
<span class='line-number'>10</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='ruby'><span class='line'><span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">generate_qr</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">text</span><span class="p">)</span>
</span><span class='line'>  <span class="nb">require</span> <span class="o">&amp;</span><span class="n">lsquo</span><span class="p">;</span><span class="n">barby</span><span class="o">&amp;</span><span class="n">rsquo</span><span class="p">;</span>
</span><span class='line'>  <span class="nb">require</span> <span class="o">&amp;</span><span class="n">lsquo</span><span class="p">;</span><span class="n">barby</span><span class="o">/</span><span class="n">barcode</span><span class="o">&amp;</span><span class="n">rsquo</span><span class="p">;</span>
</span><span class='line'>  <span class="nb">require</span> <span class="o">&amp;</span><span class="n">lsquo</span><span class="p">;</span><span class="n">barby</span><span class="o">/</span><span class="n">barcode</span><span class="o">/</span><span class="n">qr_code</span><span class="o">&amp;</span><span class="n">rsquo</span><span class="p">;</span>
</span><span class='line'>  <span class="nb">require</span> <span class="o">&amp;</span><span class="n">lsquo</span><span class="p">;</span><span class="n">barby</span><span class="o">/</span><span class="n">outputter</span><span class="o">/</span><span class="n">png_outputter</span><span class="o">&amp;</span><span class="n">rsquo</span><span class="p">;</span><span class="o">&lt;</span><span class="sr">/p&gt;</span>
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'><span class="sr">&lt;p&gt;  barcode = Barby::QrCode.new(text, level: :q, size: 5)</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="sr">  base64_output = Base64.encode64(barcode.to_png({ xdim: 5 }))</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="sr">  &amp;ldquo;data:image/</span><span class="n">png</span><span class="p">;</span><span class="n">base64</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="c1">#{base64_output}&amp;rdquo;</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="k">end</span>
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure></notextile></div></p>

<p>
  And an example call from your view:
</p>


<p><div class='bogus-wrapper'><notextile><figure class='code'> <div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='ruby'><span class='line'><span class="o">%</span><span class="n">img</span><span class="p">{</span><span class="ss">src</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="n">generate_qr</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="o">&amp;</span><span class="n">ldquo</span><span class="p">;</span><span class="o">&lt;</span><span class="n">a</span> <span class="n">href</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">&quot;http://geekhmer.github.io/&quot;</span><span class="o">&gt;</span><span class="ss">http</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="sr">//</span><span class="n">geekhmer</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">github</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">io</span><span class="o">/&lt;</span><span class="sr">/a&gt;&amp;rdquo;), class: &amp;ldquo;qr-code&amp;rdquo;}</span>
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure></notextile></div></p>

<p>
  So far so good, That's it!!! See ya!!! :)
</p>

]]></content>
